Just had an amazing meal at Bangkok Avenue and I’m still thinking about it! 
Started with their Tom Yum Soup, a bold, tangy, spicy explosion of flavor that warmed my soul. The lemongrass and chili really hit the spot 🍲🔥
Next up, the Bangkok Noodle Soup, rich, savory, and packed with authentic Thai street food vibes. That broth? Unreal. Addictive in the best way 🥢
Their Basil Fried Rice was the perfect balance, fragrant, fluffy, and full of wok-charred goodness. Simple yet so satisfying 🍚
And the Red Curry? Creamy, slightly sweet, and loaded with tender chicken and potatoes. Definitely a comfort dish I’ll be dreaming about 🥘

If you’re craving real Thai flavors, Bangkok Avenue delivers. Can’t wait to go back and try more of their menu!

#kimnstepheats_socal

Did you know the popular ramen chain in SoCal, Shin-Sen-Gumi, has a sister shop?! 🍜❤️

Torisoba Tonsho is a ramen shop that specializes in chicken ramen! I've had lots of ramen before but I never had chicken ramen until recently 🥰

Honestly Torisoba Tonsho needs more hype because the food here is chef's kiss! The ramen texture is perfectly chewy and firm while the broth is creamy, rich and full of flavor. The Original and Lemon Butter Ramen were both delicious but I preferred the lemon butter slightly more for the buttery richness and hint of acidic lemon flavor! 
I recommend ordering the value combos which comes with a bowl of ramen and a side or rice of your choice! The chicken gyoza and toriten bowl were my favorite 🤩 

Torisoba Tonsho recently added tsukemen to the menu and I'm here for it! The broth was well flavored and had a nice kick to it 🤤

Thank you for having me @torisobatonsho 💌

📍Torisoba Tonsho
349 N La Cienega Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90048

✨POV: You came for the mango sticky rice but accidentally ordered half the menu… and have no regrets💅🏻✨

If you haven’t been to Noree Thai on Beverly (sister restaurant to @luv2eat.thaibistro ), this is your sign. We pulled up hungry and left spiritually fulfilled. Highlights from our accidental banquet:

🍗 Crispy Chicken Lime Sauce – SO crispy it echoed across the table. That lime sauce is life-changing.
🥦 Chinese Broccoli with Crispy Pork – salty, savory, crunchy perfection. Honestly fighting over the last bite.
🍛 Beef Teriyaki – new to the menu and already an icon. Sweet, saucy, tender. We see you.
🦀 Crab Cream Cheese – imagine your favorite crab rangoon went to finishing school.
🍄 Crispy Cauliflower – for balance… but also fried.
🥘 Massaman Curry – rich, creamy, and basically a warm hug in a bowl.
🥭 Mango Sticky Rice – because dessert is a love language.

Do we have leftovers? Yes.
Will we be eating them cold out of the fridge while standing in the kitchen? Also yes🤭

Thank you for having me @noreethaionbeverly 

🇹🇭Noree Thai on Beverly
📍7669 Beverly Blvd,  Los Angeles, CA 90936
